HEADWORD: Aristolochiales
<hw>Aristolochiales</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>an
order of plants distinguished by tubular petaloid perianth and inferior
ovary. It includes the Aristolochiaceae, Rafflesiaceae, and
Hydnoraceae.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Aristolochiales</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
